The Executive Director:
Shall administer the Fund;
On or before May 1 of each year, and after consulting with the Commission, shall prepare operating and capital budgets for the subsequent fiscal year and submit the budgets to the Commission for review and approval;
Shall supervise the marina manager;
May execute leases of land, buildings, or facilities at Somers Cove Marina and execute contracts for events or concessions at Somers Cove Marina in accordance with subsection (c) of this section;
Subject to the approval of the Secretary, and in cooperation with the Commission, shall develop an annual master plan for the operations, maintenance, development, and improvement of Somers Cove Marina that improves services to the general boating public;
Shall administer, in cooperation with the Commission, all unencumbered grants;
Shall employ a staff to operate and maintain Somers Cove Marina, and set the staff's compensation; and
Shall, except for the marina manager, employ staff as employees of the Commission; and
Shall be an employee of the State and serve at the pleasure of the Secretary.

For goods, services, and capital improvement, design, and maintenance projects with an expected value of $5,000 to $200,000, the Executive Director shall:
Advertise the solicitation in a local newspaper and on the Somerset County website;
Issue invitations for bids to all known prospective vendors;
Tabulate and evaluate the bids;
Select for award the responsible bidder who submits the responsive bid that is the lowest bid price; and
Submit the proposed award to the Commission for review and approval.

The Commission shall:
Adopt an operating budget to use the Fund to implement the master plan;
Adopt a capital budget that may use funds from Somerset County, the City of Crisfield, the State, and other sources to implement the master plan;
Apply for grants from the Waterway Improvement Fund in accordance with Title 8, Subtitle 7 of this article; and
Subject to the Secretary's approval, receive approved grant amounts at the time of acceptance of a bid or bids for waterway improvement work;
Assess slip and other fees and charges at Somers Cove Marina as necessary in order to implement the master plan;
Set policy and provide general oversight of marina operations; and
Adopt rules and regulations necessary for the conduct of its own affairs.

The Commission may:
Accept gifts, contributions, or loans of money, supplies, goods, and services, and accept appropriations, allotments, and loans of money from:
The State or federal government;
A federal corporation;
A unit or instrumentality of the federal government; or
A political subdivision or instrumentality of the State;
Exercise a power usually possessed by a private corporation in performing similar functions unless to do so would conflict with State law; and
Do all things necessary to carry out the mandates and powers expressly provided by this section.
